{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So this is a story"},{"time":3000,"text":"of a place that I now call home."},{"time":5000,"text":"It's a story of public education"},{"time":8000,"text":"and of rural communities"},{"time":10000,"text":"and of what design might do to improve both."},{"time":13000,"text":"So this is Bertie County,"},{"time":15000,"text":"North Carolina, USA."},{"time":17000,"text":"To give you an idea of the \"where:\""},{"time":19000,"text":"So here's North Carolina, and if we zoom in,"},{"time":21000,"text":"Bertie County is in the eastern part of the state."},{"time":24000,"text":"It's about two hours east"},{"time":26000,"text":"driving-time from Raleigh."},{"time":28000,"text":"And it's very flat. It's very swampy."},{"time":30000,"text":"It's mostly farmland."},{"time":32000,"text":"The entire county"},{"time":34000,"text":"is home to just 20,000 people, and they're very sparsely distributed."},{"time":37000,"text":"So there's only 27 people per square mile,"},{"time":39000,"text":"which comes down to about 10 people"},{"time":41000,"text":"per square kilometer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"Bertie County is kind of a prime example"},{"time":46000,"text":"in the demise of rural America."},{"time":48000,"text":"We've seen this story all over the country"},{"time":51000,"text":"and even in places beyond the American borders."},{"time":54000,"text":"We know the symptoms."},{"time":56000,"text":"It's the hollowing out of small towns."},{"time":58000,"text":"It's downtowns becoming ghost towns."},{"time":60000,"text":"The brain drain --"},{"time":62000,"text":"where all of the most educated and qualified leave and never come back."},{"time":65000,"text":"It's the dependence on farm subsidies"},{"time":67000,"text":"and under-performing schools"},{"time":69000,"text":"and higher poverty rates in rural areas"},{"time":71000,"text":"than in urban."},{"time":73000,"text":"And Bertie County is no exception to this."},{"time":75000,"text":"Perhaps the biggest thing it struggles with,"},{"time":77000,"text":"like many communities similar to it,"},{"time":79000,"text":"is that there's no"},{"time":81000,"text":"shared, collective investment"},{"time":83000,"text":"in the future of rural communities."},{"time":85000,"text":"Only 6.8 percent of all our philanthropic giving in the U.S. right now"},{"time":88000,"text":"benefits rural communities,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and yet 20 percent of our population lives there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"So Bertie County is not only very rural; it's incredibly poor."},{"time":96000,"text":"It is the poorest county in the state."},{"time":98000,"text":"It has one in three of its children living in poverty,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and it's what is referred to as a \"rural ghetto.\""},{"time":104000,"text":"The economy is mostly agricultural."},{"time":107000,"text":"The biggest crops are cotton and tobacco,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and we're very proud of our Bertie County peanut."},{"time":112000,"text":"The biggest employer is the Purdue chicken processing plant."},{"time":115000,"text":"The county seat is Windsor."},{"time":117000,"text":"This is like Times Square of Windsor that you're looking at right now."},{"time":120000,"text":"It's home to only 2,000 people,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and like a lot of other small towns"},{"time":124000,"text":"it has been hollowed out over the years."},{"time":126000,"text":"There are more buildings that are empty or in disrepair"},{"time":129000,"text":"than occupied and in use."},{"time":131000,"text":"You can count the number of restaurants in the county"},{"time":133000,"text":"on one hand --"},{"time":135000,"text":"Bunn's Barbecue being my absolute favorite."},{"time":137000,"text":"But in the whole county there is no coffee shop,"},{"time":139000,"text":"there's no Internet cafe,"},{"time":141000,"text":"there's no movie theater, there's no bookstore."},{"time":143000,"text":"There isn't even a Walmart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Racially, the county"},{"time":147000,"text":"is about 60 percent African-American,"},{"time":149000,"text":"but what happens in the public schools"},{"time":151000,"text":"is most of the privileged white kids"},{"time":153000,"text":"go to the private Lawrence Academy."},{"time":155000,"text":"So the public school students"},{"time":157000,"text":"are about 86 percent African-American."},{"time":159000,"text":"And this is a spread from the local newspaper of the recent graduating class,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and you can see the difference is pretty stark."},{"time":165000,"text":"So to say that the public education system"},{"time":167000,"text":"in Bertie County is struggling"},{"time":169000,"text":"would be a huge understatement."},{"time":171000,"text":"There's basically no pool"},{"time":173000,"text":"of qualified teachers to pull from,"},{"time":175000,"text":"and only eight percent of the people in the county"},{"time":177000,"text":"have a bachelor's degree or higher."},{"time":179000,"text":"So there isn't a big legacy"},{"time":181000,"text":"in the pride of education."},{"time":183000,"text":"In fact, two years ago,"},{"time":185000,"text":"only 27 percent of all the third- through eighth-graders"},{"time":187000,"text":"were passing the state standard"},{"time":189000,"text":"in both English and math."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"So it sounds like I'm painting a really bleak picture of this place,"},{"time":195000,"text":"but I promise there is good news."},{"time":198000,"text":"The biggest asset, in my opinion,"},{"time":200000,"text":"one of the biggest assets in Bertie County right now is this man:"},{"time":202000,"text":"This is Dr. Chip Zullinger,"},{"time":204000,"text":"fondly known as Dr. Z."},{"time":207000,"text":"He was brought in in October 2007"},{"time":209000,"text":"as the new superintendent"},{"time":211000,"text":"to basically fix this broken school system."},{"time":213000,"text":"And he previously was a superintendent"},{"time":215000,"text":"in Charleston, South Carolina"},{"time":217000,"text":"and then in Denver, Colorado."},{"time":219000,"text":"He started some of the country's first charter schools"},{"time":221000,"text":"in the late '80s in the U.S."},{"time":224000,"text":"And he is an absolute renegade and a visionary,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and he is the reason that I now live and work there."},{"time":231000,"text":"So in February of 2009,"},{"time":233000,"text":"Dr. Zullinger invited us, Project H Design --"},{"time":236000,"text":"which is a non-profit design firm that I founded --"},{"time":238000,"text":"to come to Bertie and to partner with him"},{"time":240000,"text":"on the repair of this school district"},{"time":242000,"text":"and to bring a design perspective to the repair of the school district."},{"time":245000,"text":"And he invited us in particular"},{"time":247000,"text":"because we have a very specific"},{"time":249000,"text":"type of design process --"},{"time":251000,"text":"one that results in appropriate design solutions"},{"time":254000,"text":"in places that don't usually have access"},{"time":256000,"text":"to design services or creative capital."},{"time":258000,"text":"Specifically, we use these six design directives,"},{"time":261000,"text":"probably the most important being number two:"},{"time":263000,"text":"we design with, not for --"},{"time":265000,"text":"in that, when we're doing humanitarian-focused design,"},{"time":268000,"text":"it's not about designing for clients anymore."},{"time":271000,"text":"It's about designing with people,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and letting appropriate solutions emerge from within."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"So at the time of being invited down there,"},{"time":278000,"text":"we were based in San Francisco,"},{"time":280000,"text":"and so we were going back and forth"},{"time":282000,"text":"for basically the rest of 2009,"},{"time":284000,"text":"spending about half our time in Bertie County."},{"time":286000,"text":"And when I say we, I mean Project H,"},{"time":288000,"text":"but more specifically, I mean myself and my partner, Matthew Miller,"},{"time":291000,"text":"who's an architect and a sort of MacGyver-type builder."},{"time":295000,"text":"So fast-forward to today, and we now live there."},{"time":298000,"text":"I have strategically cut Matt's head out of this photo,"},{"time":300000,"text":"because he would kill me if he knew I was using it"},{"time":302000,"text":"because of the sweatsuits."},{"time":304000,"text":"But this is our front porch. We live there."},{"time":306000,"text":"We now call this place home."},{"time":308000,"text":"Over the course of this year that we spent flying back and forth,"},{"time":311000,"text":"we realized we had fallen in love with the place."},{"time":313000,"text":"We had fallen in love with the place and the people"},{"time":316000,"text":"and the work that we're able to do"},{"time":318000,"text":"in a rural place like Bertie County,"},{"time":320000,"text":"that, as designers and builders,"},{"time":322000,"text":"you can't do everywhere."},{"time":324000,"text":"There's space to experiment"},{"time":326000,"text":"and to weld and to test things."},{"time":328000,"text":"We have an amazing advocate in Dr. Zullinger."},{"time":331000,"text":"There's a nobility of real, hands-on,"},{"time":334000,"text":"dirt-under-your-fingernails work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"But beyond our personal reasons for wanting to be there,"},{"time":338000,"text":"there is a huge need."},{"time":340000,"text":"There is a total vacuum of creative capital in Bertie County."},{"time":343000,"text":"There isn't a single licensed architect in the whole county."},{"time":346000,"text":"And so we saw an opportunity"},{"time":348000,"text":"to bring design as this untouched tool,"},{"time":351000,"text":"something that Bertie County didn't otherwise have,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and to be sort of the -- to usher that in"},{"time":356000,"text":"as a new type of tool in their tool kit."},{"time":359000,"text":"The initial goal became using design"},{"time":361000,"text":"within the public education system in partnership with Dr. Zullinger --"},{"time":364000,"text":"that was why we were there."},{"time":366000,"text":"But beyond that, we recognized"},{"time":368000,"text":"that Bertie County, as a community,"},{"time":370000,"text":"was in dire need of a fresh perspective"},{"time":373000,"text":"of pride and connectedness"},{"time":375000,"text":"and of the creative capital"},{"time":377000,"text":"that they were so much lacking."},{"time":379000,"text":"So the goal became, yes, to apply design within education,"},{"time":382000,"text":"but then to figure out how to make education"},{"time":384000,"text":"a great vehicle for community development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387000,"text":"So in order to do this, we've taken three different approaches"},{"time":389000,"text":"to the intersection of design and education."},{"time":392000,"text":"And I should say that these are three things that we've done in Bertie County,"},{"time":395000,"text":"but I feel pretty confident that they could work"},{"time":397000,"text":"in a lot of other rural communities"},{"time":399000,"text":"around the U.S. and maybe even beyond."},{"time":402000,"text":"So the first of the three is design for education."},{"time":405000,"text":"This is the most kind of direct, obvious"},{"time":408000,"text":"intersection of the two things."},{"time":410000,"text":"It's the physical construction"},{"time":412000,"text":"of improved spaces and materials and experiences"},{"time":415000,"text":"for teachers and students."},{"time":417000,"text":"This is in response to the awful mobile trailers"},{"time":420000,"text":"and the outdated textbooks"},{"time":422000,"text":"and the terrible materials that we're building schools out of these days."},{"time":426000,"text":"And so this played out for us in a couple different ways."},{"time":428000,"text":"The first was a series of renovations of computer labs."},{"time":431000,"text":"So traditionally, the computer labs,"},{"time":433000,"text":"particularly in an under-performing school like Bertie County,"},{"time":436000,"text":"where they have to benchmark test every other week,"},{"time":439000,"text":"the computer lab is a kill-and-drill"},{"time":441000,"text":"testing facility."},{"time":443000,"text":"You come in, you face the wall, you take your test and you leave."},{"time":446000,"text":"So we wanted to change the way that students approach technology,"},{"time":449000,"text":"to create a more convivial and social space"},{"time":452000,"text":"that was more engaging, more accessible,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and also to increase the ability for teachers"},{"time":456000,"text":"to use these spaces for technology-based instruction."},{"time":459000,"text":"So this is the lab at the high school,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and the principal there is in love with this room."},{"time":463000,"text":"Every time he has visitors, it's the first place that he takes them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"And this also meant the co-creation with some teachers"},{"time":469000,"text":"of this educational playground system"},{"time":471000,"text":"called the learning landscape."},{"time":473000,"text":"It allows elementary-level students to learn core subjects"},{"time":476000,"text":"through game play and activity"},{"time":478000,"text":"and running around and screaming and being a kid."},{"time":480000,"text":"So this game that the kids are playing here --"},{"time":482000,"text":"in this case they were learning basic multiplication"},{"time":484000,"text":"through a game called Match Me."},{"time":486000,"text":"And in Match Me, you take the class, divide it into two teams,"},{"time":489000,"text":"one team on each side of the playground,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and the teacher will take a piece of chalk"},{"time":493000,"text":"and just write a number on each of the tires."},{"time":495000,"text":"And then she'll call out a math problem --"},{"time":497000,"text":"so let's say four times four --"},{"time":499000,"text":"and then one student from each team has to compete"},{"time":502000,"text":"to figure out that four times four is 16"},{"time":504000,"text":"and find the tire with the 16 on it and sit on it."},{"time":507000,"text":"So the goal is to have all of your teammates sitting on the tires"},{"time":509000,"text":"and then your team wins."},{"time":511000,"text":"And the impact of the learning landscape"},{"time":513000,"text":"has been pretty surprising and amazing."},{"time":515000,"text":"Some of the classes and teachers have reported higher test scores,"},{"time":518000,"text":"a greater comfort level with the material,"},{"time":520000,"text":"especially with the boys,"},{"time":522000,"text":"that in going outside and playing,"},{"time":524000,"text":"they aren't afraid to take on"},{"time":526000,"text":"a double-digit multiplication problem --"},{"time":528000,"text":"and also that the teachers are able"},{"time":530000,"text":"to use these as assessment tools"},{"time":532000,"text":"to better gauge how their students"},{"time":534000,"text":"are understanding new material."},{"time":536000,"text":"So with design for education, I think the most important thing"},{"time":539000,"text":"is to have a shared ownership of the solutions with the teachers,"},{"time":542000,"text":"so that they have the incentive and the desire to use them."},{"time":545000,"text":"So this is Mr. Perry. He's the assistant superintendent."},{"time":548000,"text":"He came out for one of our teacher-training days"},{"time":551000,"text":"and won like five rounds of Match Me in a row and was very proud of himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"So the second approach is redesigning education itself."},{"time":560000,"text":"This is the most complex."},{"time":562000,"text":"It's a systems-level look"},{"time":564000,"text":"at how education is administered"},{"time":566000,"text":"and what is being offered and to whom."},{"time":568000,"text":"So in many cases this is not so much about making change"},{"time":571000,"text":"as it is creating the conditions"},{"time":573000,"text":"under which change is possible"},{"time":575000,"text":"and the incentive to want to make change,"},{"time":577000,"text":"which is easier said than done in rural communities"},{"time":580000,"text":"and in inside-the-box education systems"},{"time":582000,"text":"in rural communities."},{"time":585000,"text":"So for us, this was a graphic public campaign"},{"time":587000,"text":"called Connect Bertie."},{"time":589000,"text":"There are thousands of these blue dots all over the county."},{"time":592000,"text":"And this was for a fund that the school district had"},{"time":594000,"text":"to put a desktop computer and a broadband Internet connection"},{"time":597000,"text":"in every home"},{"time":599000,"text":"with a child in the public school system."},{"time":601000,"text":"Right now I should say,"},{"time":603000,"text":"there are only 10 percent of the houses"},{"time":605000,"text":"that actually have an in-home Internet connection."},{"time":607000,"text":"And the only places to get WiFi"},{"time":609000,"text":"are in the school buildings, or at the Bojangles Fried Chicken joint,"},{"time":612000,"text":"which I find myself squatting outside of a lot."},{"time":615000,"text":"Aside from, you know, getting people excited"},{"time":617000,"text":"and wondering what the heck these blue dots were all over the place,"},{"time":621000,"text":"it asked the school system"},{"time":623000,"text":"to envision how it might become a catalyst"},{"time":625000,"text":"for a more connected community."},{"time":627000,"text":"It asked them to reach outside of the school walls"},{"time":630000,"text":"and to think about how they could play a role"},{"time":632000,"text":"in the community's development."},{"time":634000,"text":"So the first batch of computers"},{"time":636000,"text":"are being installed later this summer,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and we're helping Dr. Zullinger develop some strategies"},{"time":641000,"text":"around how we might connect the classroom and the home"},{"time":644000,"text":"to extend learning beyond the school day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"And then the third approach, which is what I'm most excited about,"},{"time":648000,"text":"which is where we are now,"},{"time":650000,"text":"is: design as education."},{"time":652000,"text":"So \"design as education\" means"},{"time":654000,"text":"that we could actually teach design within public schools,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and not design-based learning --"},{"time":659000,"text":"not like \"let's learn physics by building a rocket,\""},{"time":662000,"text":"but actually learning design-thinking"},{"time":665000,"text":"coupled with real construction and fabrication skills"},{"time":668000,"text":"put towards a local community purpose."},{"time":671000,"text":"It also means that designers are no longer consultants,"},{"time":673000,"text":"but we're teachers,"},{"time":675000,"text":"and we are charged with growing creative capital"},{"time":677000,"text":"within the next generation."},{"time":679000,"text":"And what design offers as an educational framework"},{"time":682000,"text":"is an antidote"},{"time":684000,"text":"to all of the boring, rigid, verbal instruction"},{"time":686000,"text":"that so many of these school districts are plagued by."},{"time":688000,"text":"It's hands-on, it's in-your-face,"},{"time":690000,"text":"it requires an active engagement,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and it allows kids to apply all the core subject learning"},{"time":695000,"text":"in real ways."},{"time":697000,"text":"So we started thinking"},{"time":699000,"text":"about the legacy of shop class"},{"time":701000,"text":"and how shop class -- wood and metal shop class in particular --"},{"time":704000,"text":"historically, has been something"},{"time":706000,"text":"intended for kids who aren't going to go to college."},{"time":708000,"text":"It's a vocational training path."},{"time":710000,"text":"It's working-class; it's blue-collar."},{"time":712000,"text":"The projects are things like,"},{"time":714000,"text":"let's make a birdhouse for your mom for Christmas."},{"time":717000,"text":"And in recent decades, a lot of the funding for shop class"},{"time":719000,"text":"has gone away entirely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721000,"text":"So we thought, what if you could bring back shop class,"},{"time":724000,"text":"but this time orient the projects"},{"time":726000,"text":"around things that the community needed,"},{"time":729000,"text":"and to infuse shop class"},{"time":731000,"text":"with a more critical and creative-design-thinking studio process."},{"time":734000,"text":"So we took this kind of nebulous idea"},{"time":736000,"text":"and have worked really closely with Dr. Zullinger for the past year"},{"time":739000,"text":"on writing this as a one-year curriculum"},{"time":742000,"text":"offered at the high school level to the junior class."},{"time":744000,"text":"And so this starts in four weeks,"},{"time":746000,"text":"at the end of the summer,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and my partner and I, Matthew and I,"},{"time":750000,"text":"just went through the arduous and totally convoluted process"},{"time":753000,"text":"of getting certified as high school teachers to actually run it."},{"time":755000,"text":"And this is what it looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"So over the course of two semesters,"},{"time":759000,"text":"the Fall and the Spring,"},{"time":761000,"text":"the students spend three hours a day every single day"},{"time":763000,"text":"in our 4,500 square foot"},{"time":765000,"text":"studio/shop space."},{"time":768000,"text":"And during that time, they're doing everything"},{"time":771000,"text":"from going out and doing ethnographic research and doing the need-finding,"},{"time":773000,"text":"coming back into the studio,"},{"time":775000,"text":"doing the brainstorming and design visualization"},{"time":777000,"text":"to come up with concepts that might work,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and then moving into the shop and actually testing them,"},{"time":781000,"text":"building them, prototyping them,"},{"time":783000,"text":"figuring out if they are going to work and refining that."},{"time":786000,"text":"And then over the summer, they're offered a summer job."},{"time":789000,"text":"They're paid as employees of Project H"},{"time":791000,"text":"to be the construction crew with us"},{"time":793000,"text":"to build these projects in the community."},{"time":795000,"text":"So the first project, which will be built next summer,"},{"time":798000,"text":"is an open-air farmers' market downtown,"},{"time":802000,"text":"followed by bus shelters for the school bus system in the second year"},{"time":805000,"text":"and home improvements for the elderly in the third year."},{"time":808000,"text":"So these are real visible projects"},{"time":810000,"text":"that hopefully the students can point to and say,"},{"time":812000,"text":"\"I built that, and I'm proud of it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"So I want you to meet three of our students."},{"time":816000,"text":"This is Ryan."},{"time":818000,"text":"She is 15 years old."},{"time":820000,"text":"She loves agriculture and wants to be a high school teacher."},{"time":823000,"text":"She wants to go to college, but she wants to come back to Bertie County,"},{"time":825000,"text":"because that's where her family is from, where she calls home,"},{"time":828000,"text":"and she feels very strongly about giving back"},{"time":830000,"text":"to this place that she's been fairly fortunate in."},{"time":833000,"text":"So what Studio H might offer her"},{"time":835000,"text":"is a way to develop skills"},{"time":837000,"text":"so that she might give back in the most meaningful way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"This is Eric. He plays for the football team."},{"time":842000,"text":"He is really into dirtbike racing,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and he wants to be an architect."},{"time":847000,"text":"So for him, Studio H offers him"},{"time":849000,"text":"a way to develop the skills he will need as an architect,"},{"time":852000,"text":"everything from drafting to wood and metal construction"},{"time":855000,"text":"to how to do research for a client."}]},{"cues":[{"time":857000,"text":"And then this is Anthony."},{"time":859000,"text":"He is 16 years old, loves hunting and fishing and being outside"},{"time":862000,"text":"and doing anything with his hands,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and so for him, Studio H means"},{"time":866000,"text":"that he can stay interested in his education"},{"time":868000,"text":"through that hands-on engagement."},{"time":870000,"text":"He's interested in forestry, but he isn't sure,"},{"time":872000,"text":"so if he ends up not going to college,"},{"time":874000,"text":"he will have developed some industry-relevant skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"What design and building really offers to public education"},{"time":879000,"text":"is a different kind of classroom."},{"time":881000,"text":"So this building downtown,"},{"time":883000,"text":"which may very well become the site of our future farmers' market,"},{"time":886000,"text":"is now the classroom."},{"time":888000,"text":"And going out into the community and interviewing your neighbors"},{"time":890000,"text":"about what kind of food they buy"},{"time":892000,"text":"and from where and why --"},{"time":894000,"text":"that's a homework assignment."},{"time":896000,"text":"And the ribbon-cutting ceremony at the end of the summer"},{"time":899000,"text":"when they have built the farmers' market and it's open to the public --"},{"time":901000,"text":"that's the final exam."},{"time":903000,"text":"And for the community, what design and building offers"},{"time":906000,"text":"is real, visible, built progress."},{"time":908000,"text":"It's one project per year,"},{"time":910000,"text":"and it makes the youth the biggest asset"},{"time":912000,"text":"and the biggest untapped resource"},{"time":914000,"text":"in imagining a new future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"So we recognize that Studio H, especially in its first year,"},{"time":920000,"text":"is a small story --"},{"time":922000,"text":"13 students, it's two teachers,"},{"time":925000,"text":"it's one project in one place."},{"time":927000,"text":"But we feel like this could work in other places."},{"time":929000,"text":"And I really, strongly believe in the power of the small story,"},{"time":932000,"text":"because it is so difficult"},{"time":934000,"text":"to do humanitarian work at a global scale."},{"time":937000,"text":"Because, when you zoom out that far,"},{"time":939000,"text":"you lose the ability to view people as humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"Ultimately, design itself is a process"},{"time":945000,"text":"of constant education"},{"time":947000,"text":"for the people that we work with and for"},{"time":949000,"text":"and for us as designers."},{"time":951000,"text":"And let's face it, designers, we need to reinvent ourselves."},{"time":954000,"text":"We need to re-educate ourselves around the things that matter,"},{"time":957000,"text":"we need to work outside of our comfort zones more,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and we need to be better citizens in our own backyard."},{"time":963000,"text":"So while this is a very small story,"},{"time":965000,"text":"we hope that it represents a step in the right direction"},{"time":968000,"text":"for the future of rural communities"},{"time":970000,"text":"and for the future of public education"},{"time":972000,"text":"and hopefully also for the future of design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}